['Increased base  strength from 16 to 18.', 'Increased base  intelligence from 16 to 18.', 'Increased base attack damage from 26-32 to 29-35.', " Moon Glaives now uses the calculated damage of the launched attack, instead of being based on Luna's average attack damage.
Previously, the damage was always fixed. For example, if Luna had an average attack damage of 100 (97-103 damage), the glaives would always deal 65/42/27/18/12/8 damage.
Now, it looks for the actual damage that got calculated for that attack. For example, when rolling 97 damage, it now deals less damage. When rolling 103, it deals more.
This also means that it works with critical strike, quell, and the backstab damage of  Shadow Blade", 'Previously, the damage was always fixed.
